list.abstract: few（[fjuː]），英文单词，作不定代词为少量；几个；没几个。作名词为少数人；特权阶层等。短语搭配有in the last few years（在过去几年里；近几年）。例句为“It took him a few minutes before Crow saw Deer caught in a trap made of ropes.（过了几分钟，乌鸦才看到鹿被绳子做成的陷阱困住了。）”。 few和little的区别为前者只修饰可数名词的复数形式，后者只修饰不可数名词。形容词性同根词为fewer，形容词类近义词为tiny、small，反义词为many。

yingyinNormal.en: Actually, just a few questions from me, Mr. Dudewitz.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我还有几个问题，杜德威茨先生。

yingyinNormal.en: After a few hours, a member of my own species found me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 几个小时后，我被一个同类发现。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, if I did run, I'd spend the next few months fundraising.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要是决定竞选，接下来几个月我就得筹款。

yingyinNormal.en: I just want to ask you a few questions about Howard Wolowitz.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我只是想问你几个关于霍华德·沃罗威茨的问题。

yingyinNormal.en: Clark. A few weeks should have passed by the time you read this.
yingyinNormal.zh: 克拉克，当你读到这封信的时候应该是几个星期之后了。

yingyinNormal.en: Phoebe, I love you. I've missed you so much these last few months.
yingyinNormal.zh: 菲比，我爱你。我过去几个月非常思念你。

yingyinNormal.en: Uh, no, not yet. There's still a few people I haven't told personally.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还没有，几个人我还没亲自告诉他们。

yingyinNormal.en: Gee, if only something existed where we could type in a few words and...
yingyinNormal.zh: 天呀，要是有这么一种东西只要输入几个词，就会...

yingyinNormal.en: There was a break-in, few months back, inside job. Your monkey was taken.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在几个月前，这里被洗劫，内贼干的，你的猴子被偷了。

yingyinNormal.en: How long have you been putting this on her? I don't know. Few weeks. Why?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你帮她擦药膏多久了? 不记得了，几个星期吧，怎么了?

yingyinNormal.en: Justice Jacobs has Alzheimer's. He came to me a few months ago to tell me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 雅各布斯法官有老年痴呆，几个月前他告诉了我。

yingyinNormal.en: So why don't we take a break. Actually, we have a few questions. Of course.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们先休息一下吧。其实我们有几个问题。请讲。

yingyinNormal.en: It must be a fragile system, if it can be brought down by just a few berries.
yingyinNormal.zh: 几个浆果就有如此大的威力，政府未免太脆弱了。

yingyinNormal.en: There are very few people out there who can claim to have out-Bonded James Bond.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这世上没几个人可以说自己比詹姆斯·邦德更厉害。

yingyinNormal.en: Must've been hard. Especially for Mother. She died a few months later. Heartbreak.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们很难接受。特别是妈妈。她在几个月后心碎而亡。

yingyinNormal.en: The math would suggest that in a few I'm a clown made of candy. But I don't dance.
yingyinNormal.zh: 根据推算，其中有几个“我”是糖娃娃，但是绝不跳舞。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, what about for a few hours? You can be my date to the ivy week party tonight.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你看离开几个小时怎么样？你今晚可以和我一起参加常青藤派对。

yingyinNormal.en: I mean, they roasted him on the spit for tapping into a few rooms at the Watergate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 就因为监听了水门大厦的几个房间，他就被人吊打。

yingyinNormal.en: You know I was thinking if we had a big fight and we broke up for a few hours. Yeah?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我在想，如果我们大吵一架，分手几个小时。嗯？

yingyinNormal.en: He went AWOL after Calantha with a few more in his outfit I wouldn't mind closing out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 卡兰塔殖民战役后他就离开了军队，当了逃兵，他所带的小队中还有几个在逃，真恨不得早点了结他们。

exam_freq_info.chinese: 不多; 很少; 没几个

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: used with plural nouns and a plural verb to mean ‘not many’
sense_info_list.zh: 不多; 很少; 没几个

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Few</highlight> of us just walk straight into the woods without a phone.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们中很少有人不带电话就直接走进树林。

examination_example.sentence: But there are <highlight>few</highlight> places where clients have more grounds for complaint than America.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是很少有其他地方的客户比美国的客户更有理由抱怨。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Few</highlight> switch DNT on now, but if tracking is off it will stay off.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 现在很少有人打开DNT（请勿追踪），但如果追踪关闭，它将保持关闭。

sense_info_list.en: used with plural nouns and a plural verb to mean ‘a small number’, ‘some’

examination_example.sentence: I've found quite a <highlight>few</highlight>, and—since I started posting them on Twitter—they have been causing quite a stir.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我发现了很多，而且从我开始在推特上发布它们以来，它们已经引起了不小的轰动。

examination_example.sentence: Here are a <highlight>few</highlight> other ways AI is aiding companies without replacing employees.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 以下是人工智能在不替换员工的情况下帮助公司的一些其他方式。

examination_example.sentence: All animals download, but only a <highlight>few</highlight> upload.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所有动物都下载，但只有一些上传。

sense_info_list.en: used with a plural verb to mean ‘a small group of people’

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>few</highlight> feed on the many.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 多数供给，少数盈利。

word_usage.usage: few作代词，表示“很少，不多”时，作主语时谓语动词要用复数形式。
only few, so few相当于few，表示否定；some few相当于some，表示肯定。

sense_info_list.en: not many but some; a small number of

examination_example.sentence: Automation is increasingly replacing jobs and leaving too <highlight>few</highlight> good new jobs behind.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 自动化正越来越多地取代工作，留下的好的新工作太少。

sense_info_list.en: used with plural nouns and a plural verb to mean 'a small number' or 'some'

examination_example.sentence: But I need to be careful with it for the next <highlight>few</highlight> weeks.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但接下来的几周我需要小心处理。

examination_example.sentence: In contrast, the small cultivator is working only a <highlight>few</highlight> acres of land.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，小耕农只耕种几英亩土地。

examination_example.sentence: Research shows that a <highlight>few</highlight> moments of conversation with a stranger creates a measurable improvement in mood.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究表明，与陌生人交谈片刻，情绪就会有明显的改善。

word_usage.usage: few 和 many 恰恰相反, 但 a good few ≈ a good many ≈ quite a few, 均表示 "很多"。

few 和 a few 都用来修饰可数名词，few“没几个”，“几乎没有”， 表示否定意义；a few "有几个”“有一些”， 表示肯定意义。
示例：(1) There are a few books on the desk.
桌上有几本书。
(2) He is very shy， he has few friends.
他很内敛，几乎没什么朋友。

few和little都可以表示否定意义“不多”“几乎没有”， 但是few 修饰可数名词，little修饰不可数名词。
示例：(1) He has few friends.
他几乎没什么朋友。
(2) I have little money.
我没有钱。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 只修饰可数名词的复数形式, 侧重指数量非常少, 给人一种模糊概念, 含否定意义。
